**Description of the problem including expected versus actual behavior**:

#### Expected 
When creating a watcher using the Elastic watcher API and using the `indices_options` section, I should not have to include all the following optional paramaters:
* allow_no_indices
* expand_wildcards
* ignore_unavailable

The docs say each of the above is optional: 
https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/7.10/indices-get-settings.html#get-index-settings-api-query-params

#### Actual
However, if `indices_options` is specified, then all of the above parameters become required. 

This was not the case in a previous version of Elasticsearch we were using (v7.6.2). 

Attempting to create a watcher with a payload that does not contain those parameters leads to errors: 
```
{
  "error" : {
    "root_cause" : [
      {
        "type" : "parse_exception",
        "reason" : "indices options xcontent did not contain expand_wildcards"
      }
    ],
    "type" : "parse_exception",
    "reason" : "could not parse [search] input for watch [tigera_secure_ee_watch.cluster.honeypod.ip.enum.test]. failed to parse [request]",
    "caused_by" : {
      "type" : "parse_exception",
      "reason" : "indices options xcontent did not contain expand_wildcards"
    }
  },
  "status" : 400
}
```

Looking at the code, this section looks like the cause: 
https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/master/server/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/action/support/IndicesOptions.java#L435-L445

